Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1

static unsigned
 ldlm_export_flock_hash(struct cfs_hash hs, const void key, unsigned mask)
 {
-       return cfs_hash_u64_hash(*(__u64 *)key, mask);
+       return cfs_hash_64(*(__u64 *)key, 0) & mask;
 }

This change in "LU-16518 misc: use fixed hash code" caused to return 0 or 1 instead of normal value. As I understand it means only 1 or 2 buckets were used instead of possible 12 or more. It could hit performance.
